      <div xml:id="LostDog"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="narrative"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="happy"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="society"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
               <l>It’s just getting dark, fog drifting in,</l>
               <l>damp grasses fragrant with anise and mint,</l>
               <l>and though I call his name</l>
               <l>until my voice cracks,</l>
               <l>there’s no faint tinkling</l>
               <l>of tag against collar, no sleek</l>
               <l>black silhouette with tall ears rushing</l>
               <l>toward me through the wild radish.</l>
               
               <l>As it turns out, he’s trotted home,</l>
               <l>tracing the route of his trusty urine.</l>
               <l>Now he sprawls on the deep red rug, not dead,</l>
               <l>not stolen by a car on West Cliff Drive.</l>
               
               <l>Every time I look at him, the wide head</l>
               <l>resting on outstretched paws,</l>
               <l>joy does another lap around the racetrack</l>
               <l>of my heart. Even in sleep</l>
               <l>when I turn over to ease my bad hip,</l>
               <l>I’m suffused with contentment.</l>
               
               <l>If I could lose him like this every day</l>
               <l>I’d be the happiest woman alive.</l>
                 
